The project will deliver a package of activity designed to increase the number of new businesses; improve the sustainability of new businesses; tackle the underrepresentation of women in the digital creative sector; provide intensive business readiness support to businesses with the characteristics and ambition for growth; and attract businesses from CWLEP’s priority sectors to the sub-region and help existing businesses to expand. In particular, it will:

• Support 324 new enterprises;
• Support 250 enterprises with their growth plans including 89 innovation-led and knowledge intensive SMEs;
• Create 294 new jobs.

